The change in the signature of the 'createLink()' method in LinkRenderer from PageContext to RenderContext breaks backwards-compatibility. This could be easily gotten around by simply providing a wrapper method like so:

public Link createLink(PageContext pageCtx, ....) {
    return createLink(pageCtx, ...);
}

It could even be deprecated if you really want. This would save having to have a 2.0-specific version of plugins for an easily avoidable reason...

