Currently the only way to exchange information between macros is to set attributes on the request. Since the request is not always available to a macro, this is a bad idea. 

Eg. if a macro like the dynamic task list outputs javascript code, you only want it to output the code once, even though there might be more than one task lists on the page. Therefore we will need to communicate between different macro calls using a boolean flag to detect whether the repeated tags have been outputted already and to skip it.

Allowing to set arbitrary attributes on the renderContext would solve this problem.

