Currently, you can create a help section in the notation guide by adding a help-section parameter to a resource or macro with a Velocity template to use. This template has access to everything in the Velocity context, including Velocity context plugin modules which can be used for dynamic content.

However, it would be useful to also allow conditions on whether or not the given section of documentation should be shown at all. This could use the existing functionality of the web UI items' Condition classes, which allows flexible permission handling and other conditions.

From the original request:

{quote}
The driving reason for this request is so that I can wiki render the documentation, using dynamic content in the documentation rather than static outputs. We have a couple of macros whose actions depend on which other plugins are installed - we also have macros who are driven off dynamic configuration (such as allowed / disallowed keywords), and it would be better for us to provide relevant information for the current install rather than outputing verbose (and unnessessary) information to the users who just want to know what they can do right there, right then.
{quote}

