I would like to be able to plug in interceptors to the stack, and specify if they are to be executed before / after a named item in the existing stack. If no item is chosen, then it defaults to a specific place. If two choose "after item x" then its random as to which plugged in interceptor is executed first - just like its random as to which plugged in spring component is initalised first.

One use for this would be a browser detection interceptor which injected browser detection JS into the page the first time it is executed (the rest would be handled by existing plugin types).

