feature request via confluence-users:

Hi, does anyone know if there is an easy way to get the {noformat}  macro to render content in a scrollable section?

I've got a few pages that use {noformat} around some log output,  that completely throws the page layout off due to the long log lines. 

It would be nice if you could just go:

{noformat:height=200px}
My really big content goes here...
{noformat}
